description:
message::extract_headers() (message.rs:23) calls String::from_utf8_lossy(raw) which copies the entire raw message — including body and attachments — into a heap String before iterating over lines. For a 10 MB message with a 20-byte Subject header, this copies ~10 MB to read ~100 bytes. The fix is to find the header/body separator (

 or 

) in raw bytes first and pass only raw[..sep] to from_utf8_lossy, or iterate over raw lines directly without full conversion.
